d schools. If every child has to attend schools that have the same standards then public schools will equalize. &#10;Trust me, I see the advantages of private schools and my wife and I are considering them for our children simply because public schools are less than desirable. &#10;That shows that the problem is self-reinforcing. Even middle income parents are willing to feel a financial pinch to avoid the problems of public schools. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="733" language="en" documentId="4753" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Fonceai" date="2nd November 2006 04:09 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=12481&amp;page=3" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4753" notes="" title="Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="243"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="244" end="415"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="416" end="577"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="578" end="733"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>